article.headline: Oklahoma 65, Kansas 49
article.story:
LAWRENCE, Kan. (AP) -- Dionnah Jackson had 19 points and Leah
Rush added 15, all in the second half, as Oklahoma beat Kansas
65-49 Wednesday night.

The first half featured seven lead changes, and Oklahoma (12-7,
4-4 Big 12) trailed 25-24 with 3:09 to play before going on a 15-0
run to take a 39-25 halftime lead.

The Sooners extended the lead early in the second half to 44-26
with 15:31 left in the game.

The Jayhawks (9-10, 2-6) then went on a 9-0 run to get within
46-35 with 11 minutes left.

Kansas' leading scorer to that point, Taylor McIntosh, fouled
out with 9:28 left, after scoring 10 points and six rebounds.
Oklahoma quickly responded as Rush scored seven points in a 9-0 run
to give the Sooners a 53-35 lead.

Besides McIntosh, Crystal Kemp was the only other Jayhawk who
scored in double-figures, with 10 points.

The Sooners were 23-of-47 (49 percent) from the field, while
holding Kansas to 18-of-50 (36 percent) shooting. Oklahoma also was
14-of-15 from the free-throw line.
